metadata.name: In Between #7
metadata.description:
In Between

Genuary is an artificially generated month of time where we build code that makes beautiful things, with 31 prompts to base your code art off. Genuary 2023 took place during the month of January 2023. Afterwards, as it happens, comes Genuary 32nd. This is an imaginary week, during which we develop one of our Genuary pieces into a 32 edition "not very long"-form generative project on fx(hash).

My Genuary 32nd project is based on Genuary 22nd: Shadows, the design of which again was based on the "art deco" pattern from day 20.

The patterns form a grid-like fence structure, dividing the space and creating an infinite cage. Light coming from the outside casts stark shadows on the floor. Several variations on halftoning techniques are used to portray tone, occasionally destroying depth perception into an abstract interplay of form.

The code of this piece has been diminished into a mere 3397 characters.

You can use the URL-parameter &m=2 as a resolution multiplier, to render images larger than your screen.

metadata.name: Spira #77
metadata.description:
Spira is a series of static pieces where lines are drawn symmetrically around a central pivot. Additionally it is possible for the piece to be "broken" in which case some of the symmetry is lost and instead a more complex asymmetrical piece is produced.

Features:
> Brokenness (A percentage to indicate how "broken" the piece is.)
> Rotation (Rotation of each iteration.)
> Palette (Colour palette.)
> Sectors (Number of sectors which form the rotational symmetry.)
> Iterations (Number of iterations - higher means more lines in each sector.)
> Spacing (The spacing between each iteration.)

Created by Lucas RiedlShah (@lucas_riedlshah)

metadata.name: Cockcoins #24
metadata.description:
Welcome to the cocktoid currency, Cockcoins! These coins can be redeemed for custom Dickgenerate art. The Dickgenerate art piece will most likely be in the style of Trebonius, which is a piece that has not debuted yet. Additional rules apply, see below:

- You must submit coins with a total of at least 100
-- every coin is worth it's face value times the multiplier from its shape
--- circle = 1
--- square = 2
--- hexagon = 3
-- one set of coins can only be redeemed for one drawing
- You can only request colors that are present within the Cockcoins you submitted
-- submitting one black coin lets you choose any colors (up to 5)
--- you can only fit so many colors into a Dickgenerative art, I will try to be accommodating

Further more, depending on the randomness of the mints I may drop the price of requesting a custom piece. The expected value of the mints is so that 100 is a fair price, but I will adjust accordingly if requests are low.

metadata.name: Glossolalia #109
metadata.description:
This series is ultimately about catharsis. The compositions can be chaotic and maybe even a little messy, but they also can be vibrant and diverse… which is really what this is trying to celebrate: diversity and expression.

Simply, it’s about the emotions associated with whatever frees you.

Please see the linked fxtext article (on the main project page) for a more in-depth dissection of the concept. It’s less of a technical discussion, and more about the experience of the artist, and how it became linked with the feelings they associate with the art.

In live mode:

For higher resolutions, you can append “&density=2” to the url to double the size, “&density=3” to triple, and so on.
(This is highly recommended.)

To adjust grain, you can append “&grain=##” to the url. 40 is the default, and 0 will remove it completely.

metadata.name: Brosser #226
metadata.description:
Exploring generative brush strokes to simulate real life paintings. 

- A selection of 19 different palettes
- 4 different drawing styles
- Randomized "color swap" between the primary and secondary colors in each palette

Several other factors determine the output of a piece, including angles, depth, brush length, and brush weight, among others.
